issue.title: [Messenger] Adding final routing key to delay queue name
issue.body:
| Q             | A
| ------------- | ---
| Branch?       | master
| Bug fix?      | yes
| New feature?  | no
| BC breaks?    | no
| Deprecations? | no
| Tests pass?   | yes
| Fixed tickets | #31241
| License       | MIT
| Doc PR        | n/a

Fixes #31241.

When we delay, we create a queue whose `x-message-ttl` matches the delay length and `x-dead-letter-routing-key` matches the original routing key used for the message. However, before this PR, the original routing key was not part of that queue's name. The result is that if two messages were delayed by the same length, but with different routing keys, the second would try to "redeclare" the existing delay queue with a new `x-dead-letter-routing-key`, resulting in an error similar to:

> Server channel error: 406, message: PRECONDITION_FAILED - inequivalent arg 'x-dead-letter-routing-key' for queue 'delay_queue_1000' 

Integration test was improved to catch this.

Cheers!

issue.title: Use alternatives for features deprecated in PHPUnit 8
issue.body:
|      Q       |   A
|------------- | -----------
| Type         | improvement
| BC Break     | no

#### Summary

- The method `assertInternalType()` is deprecated, use alternatives such as `assertIsInt()`. https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit/issues/3369
- The `$delta` parameter of `assertEquals()` is deprecated, use `assertWithDelta()` instead. https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit/issues/3341

issue.title: Deprecate optional parameters of assertFileEquals() etc.
issue.body:
The optional parameters of `$canonicalize` and `$ignoreCase` of `assertFileEquals()` etc. should have already been deprecated as part of #3341.

Migration path is described in #3949.
